-- 
Westinghouse Seeks Japan Nuclear Fuel Plants Restart, Sky Told

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-17T20:04:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/westinghouse-seeks-japan-nuclear-fuel-plants-restart-sky-told.html
Westinghouse Electric Co.’s
European President, Anders Jackson told Sky News in an interview
the company is reviewing and checking all the systems in the two
nuclear-fuel plants in  Japan  it closed after the earthquake and
subsequent tsunami and is “trying to bring them back into
operation.”  The plants were “not at all affected by the tsunami, but
it was a very severe earthquake and we want to check all systems
before we take them into operation,” Jackson said to Sky in the
interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 